	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> "According to a homily in Paris, Bibliothèque nationale de France, BnF Éthiopien d'Abbadie 179 and Collegeville, Hill Museum and Manuscript Library, MS EMML no. 1824 he was\n               a high-ranking officer in the army of Diocletian, born of John, a saint from Upper Egypt, and the pagan ʾAwsā, daughter of an\n               officer in the Roman army. Apart from this homily, in Ethiopic tradition there is also a collection of his miracles\n             preserved in Dabub Wallo, Dabra Ḥayq ʾƎsṭifānos, MS EMML no. 1939. " .
